Head
.

— Reddish-brown, impunctate. First and second basal antennomeres contrasting brown-reddish, third to outer antennomeres black (
Figs. 10
, 
15
). Ratio length of second to third antennomeres 0.75–0.88 (mean: 0.79); median to terminal antennomeres are slender, ratio length of third to fourth antennomere 0.40–0.44 (mean: 0.41; 
Fig. 11
).
